i\u00f3n|Multimedios]]\n|\n|1968\n|2.22%\n|6,942,039\n|\n|\n|Spanish\n|Spanish commercial\n|\n|-\n|[[Daystar (TV network)|Daystar]]\n|\n|1982\n|56%\n|64,736,000\n|20\n|80\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|[[SonLife Broadcasting Network]]\n|\n|2010\n|44%\n|52,096,000\n|22\n|77\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|[[TBN Enlace USA|enlace]]<ref name=\"TBN-digital-networks\">These networks are carried only on the digital subchannels of local TBN affiliates, and are owned by TBN.</ref>\n|\n|2002\n|41%\n|48,554,000\n|37\n|9\n|Spanish\n|Spanish-language religious programming\n|\n|-\n|[[Trinity Broadcasting Network|TBN]]\n|\n|1973\n|40%\n|47,360,000\n|39\n|10\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|[[Smile of a Child TV]]<ref name=\"TBN-digital-networks\" />\n|\n|2005\n|40%\n|47,360,000\n|35\n|12\n|English\n|Religious children's programming\n|\n|-\n|[[JUCE TV]]<ref name=\"TBN-digital-networks\" /><ref name=\"JCTV\">[[JCTV]] is carried on some analogue and digital television stations, digital subchannels of local [[Trinity Broadcast Network]] affiliates, and cable/satellite providers, while [[Smile of a Child]] and [[TBN Enlace USA]] are carried only on local TBN affiliates. All four networks are owned by TBN.</ref>{{small|(formerly JCTV)}}\n|\n|2003\n|40%\n|47,360,000\n|36\n|10\n|English\n|Religious youth programming/music videos\n|\n|-\n|[[Hillsong Channel]]<ref name=\"TBN-digital-networks\" />\n|\n|2002\n|40%\n|47,360,000\n|35\n|9\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|[[Three Angels Broadcasting Network|3ABN]]\n|\n|1984\n|27%\n|31,968,000\n|2\n|133\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|3ABN Latino\n|\n|2003\n|20%\n|23,680,000\n|0\n|124\n|Spanish\n|Spanish religious\n|\n|-\n|[[Peace TV]]\n|\n|2006\n|15%\n|17,760,000\n|0\n|7\n|English\n|Religious (Islamic)\n|\n|-\n|[[Dare to Dream Network]]\n|\n|2010\n|13%\n|15,392,000\n|0\n|101\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|[[Three Angels Broadcasting Network|3ABN Proclaim!]]\n|\n|2010\n|13%\n|15,392,000\n|0\n|109\n|English\n|Religious\n|\n|-\n|[[Almavision]]\n|\n|2002\